      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(server): send one response.create after all multi-tool outputs",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- When `response.done` contains multiple `function_call` items (e.g. `query_agent` + `save_call_report`, or two agent queries), the previous loop sent one `response.create` per tool. The second call would fail with _\"already has an active response\"_, silencing the model's follow-up turn.\n- Fix: collect all `function_call_output` items inside the loop, then send a single `response.create` once all outputs are queued.\n- A `hasOutput` flag gates the final send so a response with only non-function-call output items (or a cancelled response caught earlier) does not trigger an unnecessary `response.create`.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nThe fix is deterministic and fully covered by the injected-socket test harness — no live OpenAI session needed.\n\nBefore the fix, the multi-tool test emitting two `save_call_report` calls in one `response.done` produced **two** `response.create` events (the second would error at runtime). After the fix, exactly **one** is produced.\n\n```\n# Subtest: a response with multiple tool calls sends exactly one response.create\nok 1 - a response with multiple tool calls sends exactly one response.create\n# Subtest: a response with a single tool call still sends one response.create\nok 2 - a response with a single tool call still sends one response.create\n```\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `pnpm run lint`\n- [x] `pnpm run typecheck`\n- [x] `pnpm test` — 58/58 passing, including:\n  - `test/server-multi-tool.test.ts` — multi-tool response emits exactly one `response.create`; single-tool response still emits one `response.create`\n- [x] `pnpm run build`\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
        "branch": "fix/multi-tool-response-create",
